
[1]nocturnal

   NOCTURN'AL, a. [L. night.]

   1. Pertaining to night; as nocturnal darkness.

   2. Done or happening at night; as a nocturnal expedition or assault; a
   nocturnal visit.

   3. Nightly; done or being every night.

   From gilded roofs depending lamps display nocturnal beams, that emulate
   the day.

   NOCTURN'AL, n. An instrument, chiefly used at sea to take the altitude
    of stars about the pole, in order to ascertain the latitude. This may
     be a hemisphere, or a planisphere on the plane of the equinoctial.
